\par \pard\plain \s6\li360\sa31 \f2\fs16 The object of Cruel is to move all the cards in order, from Ace to King, to the corresponding four suit stacks.  The following section explains how to play the game.
\par \pard \s6\li360\sa31 
\par \pard\plain \s13\sa86 \b\f2\fs16\cf2 To Start a New Game:
\par \pard\plain \s7\fi-360\li720\sa180\tx720 \f2\fs16 \{bmc blkarow.bmp\}\tab From the Game menu, choose New, or press {\fs12 F2}.
\par \pard\plain \s13\sa86 \b\f2\fs16\cf2 To Move a Card:
\par \pard\plain \s14\fi-360\li720\sa43\tx720 \f2\fs16 1\tab Point to a card.
\par \pard\plain \s7\fi-360\li720\sa180\tx720 \f2\fs16 2\tab Drag the card to its new location.
\par \pard\plain \s17\li360\sb60\sa187 \f2\fs16 {\cf6 Note:}  You can also move a card from one of the stacks below up to a suit stack by double-clicking the card.
\par \pard\plain \s13\sa86 \b\f2\fs16\cf2 To Re-deal the Cards:
\par \pard\plain \s7\fi-360\li720\sa180\tx720 \f2\fs16 \{bmc blkarow.bmp\}\tab Click the Deal button.
\par \pard\plain \s13\sa86 \b\f2\fs16\cf2 To Back Up a Move:
\par \pard\plain \s7\fi-360\li720\sa180\tx720 \f2\fs16 \{bmc blkarow.bmp\}\tab From the Game menu, choose Backup, or press the BACKSPACE key.
